HJR86 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 COMMENDING TOBIN ROTH ON BEING INSTALLED AS THE
4 INTERNATIONAL PRESIDENT OF THETA CHI FRATERNITY.
5
6 WHEREAS, Tobin "Toby" Roth was installed as
7 International President of Theta Chi Fraternity on August 5,
8 2024, during the 168th Anniversary Convention in New
9 Orleans, Louisiana; and
10 WHEREAS, Mr. Roth has faithfully served on Theta
11 Chi's Grand Chapter since 2018 in several key leadership
12 roles, including International Vice President, International
13 Chaplain, and International Marshal; and
14 WHEREAS, Theta Chi Fraternity, one of the oldest
15 men's collegiate fraternities in North America, was founded
16 in 1856 and has initiated more than 200,000 members and
17 established 245 chapters with the mission of developing
18 college-age men into successful students, good citizens,
19 lifelong brothers, and resolute leaders; and
20 WHEREAS, Mr. Roth was initiated into the Alpha Phi
21 Chapter of Theta Chi Fraternity at The University of
22 Alabama, where the bonds of brotherhood, personal
23 development, and leadership were first instilled in him; and
24 WHEREAS, prior to joining the Grand Chapter, Mr. Roth
25 served as House Corporation President for the Alpha Phi
26 Chapter from 2014 to 2018 and was an alumni delegate at the
27 158th Anniversary Convention in 2014; and
28 WHEREAS, as an undergraduate, Mr. Roth held the
Page 1

WHEREAS, as an undergraduate, Mr. Roth held the
HJR86 Enrolled
29 positions of Vice President and Scholarship Chair of the
30 Alpha Phi Chapter and served as a collegiate delegate to the
31 132nd Anniversary Convention in 1988, where he received the
32 prestigious Key Man Award; in 1990, he was honored as "Greek
33 Man of the Year" by the Order of Omega as the outstanding
34 senior fraternity man at The University of Alabama; and
35 WHEREAS, in his role as International President, Mr.
36 Roth continues to uphold and embody the ideals and values of
37 Theta Chi Fraternity by dedicating his time, energy, and
38 talents to supporting its members and chapters nationwide;
39 now therefore,
40 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
41 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That Tobin "Toby" Roth be
42 formally and enthusiastically commended for his lifelong
43 dedication to Theta Chi Fraternity and congratulated on his
44 installation as International President, with deep
45 appreciation for his outstanding leadership, character, and
46 unwavering commitment to the brotherhood.
